 writes: The heat death of the Universe is the idea that increasing 
entropy will eventually cause the Universe to arrive at a uniformly, 
maximally disordered state. Every piece of evidence we have points 
towards our unfortunate, inevitable trending towards that end, with 
every burning star, every gravitational merger, and even every breath 
we, ourselves, take. Yet even while we head towards this fate, it may be
 possible for intelligence in an artificial form to continue in the 
Universe for an extraordinarily long time: possibly for as long as a 
googol years, but not quite indefinitely. Eventually, it all must end.<p xml:base="https://d186loudes4jlv.cloudfront.net/ruby/slashdot.xml"></p><div class="share_submission" xml:base="https://d186loudes4jlv.cloudfront.net/ruby/slashdot.xml">
